Saudi Investment Bank Cuts Fourth-Quarter Loan Provisions by 89%

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-02-12T08:30:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-12/saudi-investment-bank-cuts-fourth-quarter-loan-provisions-by-89-.html
  Saudi Investment Bank  said
provisions for bad loans in the fourth quarter fell 89 percent
from the year-earlier period.  Provisions declined to 50 million riyals ($13.3 million) in
the three months ended Dec. 31, from 434.6 million riyals a year
earlier, according to data posted on the  Saudi bourse  website on
Feb. 9. Full-year provisions increased 52 percent to 845 million
riyals.  On Jan. 15, Saudi Investment reported a fourth-quarter
profit of 238 million riyals after a loss of 109 million riyals
in the year-earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at   shajimathew@bloomberg.net  